# Logging Standards

## Context
- When writing console.log, console.error, console.warn statements
- When adding debug or informational output
- When logging application events or errors

## Requirements
- Use hybrid format: readable message + key=value pairs for data
- NO emojis in any log messages
- Include relevant context as key=value pairs
- Use consistent log levels (info, error, warn, debug)
- Keep messages human-readable and actionable
- Include service=, error=, count=, etc. for structured data

## Examples
<example>
console.log('Starting email processing count=5 status=started');
console.log('Connected to Gmail service=gmail status=success');
console.error('Failed to create transaction error="Invalid amount" id=123 status=failed');
</example>

